# DBA Workflow (Current)

## Runtime DB model
- Primary DB: PostgreSQL (container `postgres`).
- Access via `docker compose exec -T postgres psql ...`.
- SQLite is legacy-only and not runtime source of truth.

## Migration policy
- All runtime schema updates go through Alembic in `alembic_migrations/versions`.
- New migration must include safe guards for repeated execution where possible.
- Never edit old applied migration revisions.

## Data safety policy
- Before server migration: create compressed `pg_dump` backup.
- Never run destructive DDL/DML on production without explicit approval.
- For data sync between envs, prefer targeted entity transfer over full DB overwrite.

## Verification after migration
- check migration logs in `app`
- confirm critical tables/columns exist using `information_schema`
- run one feature-level API check for affected module
